# Commit local database

This repo tracks the root SQLite database in git. Always include it when committing and pushing.

## What to commit

- `db.sqlite3` at the project root whenever it changed (migrations, imports, bootstrap, admin edits, tests that touch the DB, etc.)
- Do not commit other `*.sqlite3` files (they stay ignored)

## Git workflow

When the user asks for a commit (or you commit after implementation):

1. Stage application code **and** `db.sqlite3` if it differs from `HEAD`
2. Never omit `db.sqlite3` from a push because it is "local data" — here it is the shared dev dataset
3. `.gitignore` already allows only `db.sqlite3` via `!db.sqlite3` under `*.sqlite3`

## If only the database changed

A commit with only `db.sqlite3` is valid when data was updated without code changes (imports, manual fixes, `bootstrap_local_data`).
